\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 41. T. patens} Schreber in Sturm,{\i   Deutschl. Fl.} Abt. 1, Band 4, Heft 16 (1804). Annual, sparsely hairy; stems 20-50 cm, flexuous, erect or ascending. Leaflets up to 18 mm, narrowly elliptic-obovate, the terminal subsessile or with a petiolule up to 2 mm. Stipules ovate, dilated and rounded at the base. Heads 10-15 mm in fruit; peduncles 20-50 mm, slender, usually much longer than the leaves. Flowers almost sessile. Upper calyx-teeth shorter than the upper limb of the calyx-tube; lower calyx-teeth equal to or longer than the lower limb of the calyx-tube. Corolla 5-7 mm, yellow; limb of standard oblong-ovate, sulcate.{\i   Moist grassland. C. & S. Europe.} Al Au Bu Co Cr Cz Ga Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Tu.
