\pard\f0\fs28     {\b 45. T. sebastianii} Savi,{\i   Diar. Med. Flajani }2 (1815). Annual; 5-30 cm, sparsely hairy, erect or ascending. Leaflets up to 18 mm, obovate-lanceolate or oblong, with 15-25 pairs of lateral veins; petiolules subequal, very short. Heads 8-10 mm, 8- to 20-flowered; pedicels deflexed, 2-4 times as long as the calyx-tube. Upper calyx-teeth 2-3 times as long as upper limb of calyx-tube; lower calyx-teeth 3-4 times as long as the lower limb of the calyx-tube. Corolla 4 mm, yellow, becoming reddish-brown after anthesis; limb of standard broadly obovate or orbicular, sulcate.{\i   C. & S. Italy, Sicilia; Balkan peninsula, very local.} Bu Gr It Ju Si Tu.
